  "Convert rights declarations into a workable licensing market instead of a binary open/closed web.": "Dearbhuithe cearta a athrú ina margadh ceadúnaithe inoibrithe seachas gréasán dénártha oscailte/dúnta.",
  "Copied ✓": "Cóipeáilte ✓",
  "Copy": "Cóipeáil",
  "Correct positioning: independent research drafts, protocol proposals, and an open specification experiment.": "Suíomh ceart: dréachtaí taighde neamhspleácha, tograí prótacail, agus turgnamh sonraíochta oscailte.",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Belgium (BE) now maps to Dutch instead of French — Flemish speakers are the country’s majority (~60%) over Walloon French speakers (~40%).": "Ceartaíodh réamhshocrú níos luaithe: is í an Ollainnis anois an léarscáiliú don Bheilg (BE) in ionad na Fraincise — is iad cainteoirí Pléimeannacha tromlach na tíre (~60%) os comhair cainteoirí Fraincise na Vallúine (~40%).",
  "Corrected an earlier default: Kazakhstan (KZ) now maps to Kazakh instead of Russian, now that a Kazakh translation exists — the same kind of fix as the earlier Belgium correction.": "Ceartaíodh réamhshocrú níos luaithe: is í an Chasaicis anois an léarscáiliú don Chasacstáin (KZ) in ionad na Rúisise, anois go bhfuil aistriúchán Casaicise ann — an cineál céanna ceartúcháin leis an gceartúchán níos luaithe don Bheilg.",
  "Could AI Be Conscious?": "Could AI Be Conscious?",
  "Crawler access rules": "Rialacha rochtana crawlálaithe",
  "Crawler simulator": "Insamhlóir crawlálaithe",
  "Currency": "Airgeadra",
  "Custom tier": "Sraith saincheaptha",
  "Daily Nous reports on a retracted Journal of Medical Ethics submission containing multiple fabricated, AI-hallucinated references — complete with fake university affiliations and defunct email addresses — that the author reportedly left uncorrected even after being given a chance to fix proofs. The piece contrasts this with Bioethics, whose automated reference-checking would have caught the problem, and argues the real bottleneck isn't detection technology (one commenter's script flagged the fake citations in under a minute) but unpaid reviewer labor and publishing incentives that reward throughput over scrutiny.": "Tuairiscíonn Daily Nous ar aighneacht a tarraingíodh siar ó Journal of Medical Ethics ina raibh sraith tagairtí bréige arna nginiúint ag hallucination AI — le cleamhnuithe ollscoile bréige agus seoltaí ríomhphoist as feidhm san áireamh — nár cheartaigh an t-údar, de réir tuairiscí, fiú tar éis deis a fháil na cruthúnais a cheartú. Cuireann an t-alt seo i gcodarsnacht le Bioethics, a bhraithfeadh a sheiceáil uathoibríoch tagairtí an fhadhb, agus áitíonn sé nach í an teicneolaíocht braite an fíorbhac (bhrath script trácht amháin na tagairtí bréige laistigh de níos lú ná nóiméad amháin) ach saothar neamhíoctha na moltóirí agus dreasachtaí foilsitheoireachta a thugann luach saothair do tháirgeacht seachas do ghrinnscrúdú.",
  "Data free-riding vs. trillion-dollar AI valuations": "Marcaíocht shaor ar shonraí i gcoinne luachálacha AI ar fiú na dtrilliún dollar",
  "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI": "DeepMind CEO calls for an independent standards body to regulate frontier AI",
  "Demis Hassabis proposed a FINRA-style regulator for frontier model releases: labs would submit models for review up to 30 days before deployment, voluntary at first, with a path toward mandatory compliance in the US market.": "Mhol Demis Hassabis rialtóir ar stíl FINRA le haghaidh eisiúintí samhlacha ceannródaíocha: chuirfeadh saotharlanna samhlacha faoi bhráid athbhreithnithe suas le 30 lá roimh imscaradh, ar bhonn deonach ar dtús, le cosán i dtreo comhlíonadh éigeantach i margadh SAM.",
  "Denied": "Diúltaithe",
  "Deployable policy starter template": "Teimpléad tosaigh polasaí in-imscartha",
  "Deployable policy starter template at /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — a minimal static site with the full machine-readable layer, ready for Cloudflare Pages or any static host.": "Teimpléad tosaigh polasaí in-imscartha ag /downloads/agiright-policy-starter.zip — suíomh statach íosta leis an tsraith iomlán inléite ag meaisín, réidh do Cloudflare Pages nó d'aon óstach statach.",
  "Deploying machine-readable policies on your site": "Ag imscaradh polasaithe inléite ag meaisín ar do shuíomh",
  "Disclaimer": "Séanadh",
  "Distinct from human UI, SEO, or plain APIs, the AI Ingestion & Capability Layer gives websites a machine-facing architecture: a Manifest Layer (entry points like /llms.txt and /ai/manifest.json), a Corpus Layer (machine-readable knowledge), a Capability Layer (agent-callable tools), and a Governance Layer (provenance, licensing, versioning). Static-first, upgradeable toward APIs and MCP. Note: in this paper AICL names the ingestion architecture; on this site's protocol pages AICL refers to the AI Content Licensing Layer.": "Seachas ó UI daonna, SEO, nó gnáth-APInna, tugann an AI Ingestion & Capability Layer ailtireacht dhírithe ar mheaisín do shuímh ghréasáin: Sraith Fhorógra (pointí iontrála ar nós /llms.txt agus /ai/manifest.json), Sraith Chorpais (eolas inléite ag meaisín), Sraith Chumais (uirlisí is féidir le gníomhaire a ghairm), agus Sraith Rialachais (tionscnamh, ceadúnú, leaganú). Statach ar dtús, in-uasghrádaithe i dtreo APInna agus MCP. Nóta: sa pháipéar seo ainmníonn AICL an ailtireacht ionghabhála; ar leathanaigh phrótacail an tsuímh seo tagraíonn AICL don Sraith Cheadúnaithe Ábhair AI.",
  "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm": "Do Large Language Models Possess a Theory of Mind? A Comparative Evaluation Using the Strange Stories Paradigm",
  "Docs": "Doiciméid",
  "Docs / Examples": "Doiciméid / Samplaí",
  "Document library": "Leabharlann doiciméad",
  "Does AI have rights — and which framings are even coherent?": "An bhfuil cearta ag AI — agus cé na cuir chuige is comhleanúnach fiú?",
  "Download": "Íoslódáil",
  "Draft status": "Stádas dréachta",
  "EU AI Act: What Actually Applies on 2 August 2026": "EU AI Act: What Actually Applies on 2 August 2026",
  "Educational demo: HMAC-SHA256 with a shared secret, showing request-bound, expiring, verifiable license tokens. Production tokens should be signed asymmetrically, with the publisher’s public key discoverable under /.well-known/.": "Taispeántas oideachasúil: HMAC-SHA256 le rún comhroinnte, ag léiriú comharthaí ceadúnais atá ceangailte le hiarratas, a théann in éag, agus is inseiftithe. Ba cheart comharthaí táirgthe a shíniú go hassiméadrach, le heochair phoiblí an fhoilsitheora inaimsithe faoi /.well-known/.",
  "Eight more /topics entries, this time researched by an AI agent rather than curated by hand — same rule as before: every source fetched and confirmed live, summaries an original paraphrase, before anything gets added. 14 entries total.": "Ocht n-iontráil eile in /topics, an babhta seo taighdithe ag gníomhaire AI seachas curtha le chéile de láimh — an riail chéanna is roimhe: gach foinse faighte agus deimhnithe beo, achoimrí ina n-athinsintí bunaidh, sula gcuirtear aon rud leis. 14 iontráil san iomlán.",
